Edicts						KEY:Order of the First Law ~ Edicts						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality																DESC:The cavalier must strive to protect atheists and all those who reject the gods. He must never have a patron deity or willingly serve agents of the divine. He must protect the common folk from suffering due to the actions of divine agents.
Rejection of Faith				KEY:Order of the First Law ~ Rejection of Faith				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:CavalierClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:At 2nd level, the cavalier must refuse all divine magic, including helpful effects or spells. As long as he has not benefited from divine magic in the past 24 hours, he receives a +2 morale bonus on one saving throw of his choice. Each day he can change the saving throw to which this bonus applies.
Threat of Reason					KEY:Order of the First Law ~ Threat of Reason				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:CavalierClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:At 8th level, whenever the cavalier threatens a space occupied by a divine spellcaster, the spellcaster must add 4 to the DC of any concentration checks, dispel checks, or caster level checks she attempts.
Godslayer						KEY:Order of the First Law ~ Godslayer					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:CavalierClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:At 15th level, whenever the cavalier makes a melee attack against the target of his challenge and that target is a divine spellcaster, the cavalier gains a +%1 bonus on attack and damage rolls. This damage is multiplied on a critical hit.|CHA

